@rabbah - to clarify your CORS related comment above.  this is in reference to a couple lines that look like
```val allowHeaders = `Access-Control-Allow-Headers`("Authorization", "Content-Type", "User-Agent")```

if this is not place, would web apps issuing cross origin api requests (implemented by web actions) still be allowed to provide a user agent header in the request?

Or, instead of SPI, we can configure Akka as:
```javascript
cluster {
    name: "my-akka-cluster",
    discovery {
      source: "ansible | mesos | kubernetes", 
    }
   ...
  }
```
And provide an impl for each discovery source. 

This configuration will become more and more important as we bring more clustering capabilities  into the project.

